[Prompt for ChatGPT]
-Can you please make a bash script to use on linux mint to do the following things when I run it?
-You may ask my as many questions you want so that the instructions are clear to you so that you may help me with this and do the necessary.


[Instructions]
-Disable repository restrictions with the help of this by adding "#" to the second line of code:
"sudo nano /etc/apt/sources.list"

-Run this command:
"sudo apt update"

-Install every .deb file from the following location:
"/home/mint/Downloads/System Customization/AppImages & .deb files"

-Ask if I want to install the following deb files:
"/home/mint/Downloads/System Customization/AppImages & .deb files/Optional Debs/jp2a_1.1.1-2ubuntu2_amd64.deb"
"/home/mint/Downloads/System Customization/AppImages & .deb files/Optional Debs/imagemagick_6.9.12.98+dfsg1-5.2build2_amd64.deb"

-Ask if I want to install chafa, then run the following command:
sudo apt install chafa
(along with all its dependencies)

-Install conky and conky manager2 with the help of these commands:
"sudo add-apt-repository ppa:teejee2008/foss"
"sudo apt update"
"sudo apt install conky-manager2"
(If conky is not installed using the above commands, install it using this deb file: "/home/mint/Downloads/System Customization/AppImages & .deb files/Optional Debs/conky-manager2_2.72_amd64.deb")
(Add a fallback option when installing conky, if the PPAs aren't working, install from the provided deb file instead)

-Ask before installing.
-Run this command to install ohmyposh:
"curl -s https://ohmyposh.dev/install.sh | bash -s"


[This applies to everything]-"Important"
-Ask everything at the start of the script.
